attributes.Long form description: The student is taking apart a wheeled cart. They unscrew the wheels, then the hexagon cap nuts on the trays, then the right hexagon cap nut and bracket from the top tray. They remove the top and middle trays. They do the same for the bottom tray. They unscrew the side bars and disassemble the side bars and base frame. They split the bars on the right side, then the left side.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the first wheel.
The student disassembles the second wheel.
The student disassembles the third wheel.
The student disassembles the fourth wheel.
The student unscrews the left hexagon cap nut of the middle tray.
The student unscrews the right hexagon cap nut of the middle tray.
The student unscrews the left hexagon cap nut and bracket from the top tray.
The student unscrews the right hexagon cap nut and bracket from the top tray.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Accidentally, the student drops the wrench into the floor.

The student removes the grid tray at the bottom.
